      "content": "The climate crisis is an undeniable emergency, and congestion pricing is one of the most effective, proven tools to combat it. Any policy that demonstrably reduces tailpipe emissions and forces a shift toward cleaner transit is a necessary step toward a livable future. The environmental imperative is so strong that the economic arguments against it are often used as excuses by those resistant to necessary change. Therefore, the environmental necessity makes the implementation of congestion pricing a moral and practical obligation.",
      "source": "target",
